to school of medicine faculty and staff from marcia cohen senior associate dean for finance and administration subject winter closure 2012 dear colleagues i m writing to inform you of the school of medicine's 2012 winter closure schedule for the december 2012 holiday season the school of medicine will follow the same schedule approved by president hennessy and provost etchemendy for the university the 2012 winter closure will be monday december 24 2012 through friday january 4 2013 regular operations will resume on monday january 7 2013 the closure period was based on several factors including the challenges of closing individual units and the cost of additional paid days off as well as providing an uninterrupted break for employees and aligning our winter break with that of most other school grade k 12 breaks in the area the winter closure will also apply to bargaining unit employees during the winter closure the following dates have been designated as university holidays monday december 24 2012 tuesday december 25 2012 tuesday january 1 2013 last year the university provided one additional paid day off during the winter close period this year the university will provide three 3 additional days off with pay which the school of medicine has designated as december 26 27 and 28 2012 for the other four 4 regular workdays during winter close that are not designated by the university as holidays or a paid day off employees may use accrued vacation time any available pto approved time off without pay or any combination thereof all departments are asked to administer time off during this week in a consistent fashion and not to award university paid time off for other dates to summarize the two week closure is as follows monday december 24 2012 university holiday tuesday december 25 2012 university holiday wednesday december 26 2012 additional paid day off thursday december 27 2012 additional paid day off friday december 28 2012 additional paid day off monday december 31 2012 vacation pto unpaid time off tuesday january 1 2013 university holiday wednesday january 2 2013 vacation pto unpaid time off thursday january 3 2013 vacation pto unpaid time off friday january 4 2013 vacation pto unpaid time off all areas of the school of medicine are asked to close during this two week period as in past years there will be some areas that must remain open for all or part of the winter closure ie clinical units lab animal facilities some research labs portions of student affairs lane library etc dfa's or department directors are expected to review requests for employees to work during winter closure and approve only those that are critical to departmental operations any decision to keep a department open must be approved by the dfa and or department director overseeing the department and hrg employee relations must be notified in those rare cases where operations require that some employees remain on duty in a unit that is otherwise closed hrg employee relations in conjunction with the dfa and or department director may approve an alternative paid day off for those employees who are required to work on any of the designated paid days off december 26 27 or 28 2012 for operational reasons please inform all your employees as soon as possible of your department plans so that they make appropriate plans for the use of their accrued vacation and pto if you have questions regarding the school of medicine winter closure schedule please contact hrg employee relations at 725 8615 or you may reply to this email and your question will be directed to an hrg staff member for response cc philip pizzo md cori bossenberry
